00:12:52,972 --> 00:12:56,142
And we also wanted to show that

250
00:12:56,709 --> 00:13:00,713
Genki was participating in
the concert along with us.

251
00:13:00,880 --> 00:13:03,015
That's why we wanted to start

252
00:13:03,816 --> 00:13:07,987
the video with a scene of us
watering pink flowers.

253
00:13:12,792 --> 00:13:14,493
JULY 18, 2019
YOKOHAMA ARENA

254
00:13:14,560 --> 00:13:16,061
<i>And in July...</i>

255
00:13:16,629 --> 00:13:20,132
<i>it's one day before the opening day
of their second-year concert tour.</i>

256
00:13:23,435 --> 00:13:24,470
<i>They will once again</i>

257
00:13:24,804 --> 00:13:29,542
<i>stand on the same stage they stood on
when they debuted one year ago.</i>

258
00:13:30,476 --> 00:13:32,011
-What number?
-Eight!

259
00:13:33,179 --> 00:13:34,346
Amazing.

260
00:13:34,914 --> 00:13:37,149
Seeing this makes me so excited.

261
00:13:40,019 --> 00:13:41,620
<i>The difference is,</i>

262
00:13:41,887 --> 00:13:45,324
<i>they will be using many more
large-scale special effects.</i>

263
00:13:47,593 --> 00:13:50,529
<i>Many of which were suggested
by the members themselves.</i>

264
00:13:52,198 --> 00:13:53,232
It's rotating.

265
00:13:53,299 --> 00:13:54,466
Rotating.

266
00:13:56,402 --> 00:13:58,838
<i>The set on the main stage
is able to rotate</i>

267
00:13:59,038 --> 00:14:01,040
<i>to show two different designs.</i>

268
00:14:02,741 --> 00:14:06,579
<i>The classic idol image
and the mature King & Prince...</i>

269
00:14:06,745 --> 00:14:09,381
<i>Both of their characters
can be portrayed this way.</i>

270
00:14:10,616 --> 00:14:12,651
Can we stop here for a moment

271
00:14:12,718 --> 00:14:15,187
and perform this song here for a second?

272
00:14:16,055 --> 00:14:17,122
Sure.

273
00:14:20,759 --> 00:14:23,262
<i>Almost all of the members' requests</i>

274
00:14:23,529 --> 00:14:26,065
<i>for stage production
have been fulfilled by the staff.</i>

275
00:14:29,101 --> 00:14:31,837
<i>As they go through trial and error,</i>

276
00:14:32,071 --> 00:14:34,073
<i>they feel the weight of responsibility.</i>

277
00:14:42,248 --> 00:14:44,884
-The stage effects are pretty crazy.
-I know.

278
00:14:44,950 --> 00:14:47,152
I mean, the set itself flips.

279
00:14:47,419 --> 00:14:50,756
You only really see
a set flip like that in a theater.

280
00:14:50,823 --> 00:14:52,224
That's why

281
00:14:52,291 --> 00:14:56,962
I think we can surprise
the people who see it.

282
00:14:57,396 --> 00:14:58,364
<i>However,</i>

283
00:14:58,430 --> 00:15:00,799
<i>this time, there was more than that.</i>

284
00:15:01,033 --> 00:15:02,468
-Here we go.
-Okay.

285
00:15:04,169 --> 00:15:09,241
<i>The center stage will spin
above the audience like a giant propeller.</i>

286
00:15:13,412 --> 00:15:15,948
<i>The members will stand on a glass floor.</i>

287
00:15:16,515 --> 00:15:19,585
<i>It's been made so that the audience
can see them from below.</i>

288
00:15:21,921 --> 00:15:24,590
King & Prince, it's time to move.

289
00:15:25,357 --> 00:15:26,825
Will you keep to the right?

290
00:15:27,092 --> 00:15:29,228
-Pick a side.
-Right.

291
00:15:30,062 --> 00:15:32,998
<i>This is when tensions begin to rise.</i>

292
00:15:33,799 --> 00:15:35,534
The members are in the front.

293
00:15:35,768 --> 00:15:37,503
The members are facing us.

294
00:15:37,870 --> 00:15:40,839
Just a moment. Okay.

295
00:15:42,942 --> 00:15:45,210
{\an8}<i>ARASHI's Jun Matsumoto.</i>

296
00:15:46,178 --> 00:15:50,115
{\an8}<i>The members of King & Prince asked him
to help with stage directing,</i>

297
00:15:50,249 --> 00:15:53,419
{\an8}<i>so he is here to do a final check
for his assigned block.</i>

298
00:15:55,854 --> 00:15:57,489
Be ready for it to spin.

299
00:15:58,157 --> 00:15:58,991
Go.

300
00:16:01,694 --> 00:16:06,332
<i>Matsumoto's eyes have been trained
from directing years of ARASHI's concerts.</i>

301
00:16:06,999 --> 00:16:08,701
<i>Where will he be looking?</i>

302
00:16:09,568 --> 00:16:11,337
Is this the actual speed?

303
00:16:11,403 --> 00:16:13,038
Yes, it is.

304
00:16:13,872 --> 00:16:15,507
Go to your bridge positions.

305
00:16:16,442 --> 00:16:17,643
Bridge positions? Okay.

306
00:16:20,579 --> 00:16:22,348
The bridge starts around here.

307
00:16:22,414 --> 00:16:23,482
Ready...

308
00:16:25,985 --> 00:16:28,087
<i>How far each member is from each other</i>

309
00:16:28,153 --> 00:16:29,855
<i>and when they begin moving...</i>

310
00:16:30,656 --> 00:16:34,760
<i>He thoroughly checks how
they will be seen by the audience.</i>

311
00:16:37,363 --> 00:16:39,932
Make sure the cameras
are directly underneath.

312
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:44,303
Right now, Sho is...

313
00:16:44,370 --> 00:16:46,939
<i>He lives by the phrase,
"the devil's in the detail"</i>

314
00:16:47,239 --> 00:16:48,907
<i>and makes slight changes.</i>

315
00:16:49,708 --> 00:16:52,344
-I see.
-I want it to touch.

316
00:16:53,412 --> 00:16:54,580
Oh, sorry.

317
00:16:54,646 --> 00:16:57,049
I want that part to be a little tighter.

318
00:16:57,116 --> 00:16:59,018
At the end. Right there.

319
00:17:00,252 --> 00:17:01,687
Are there two lines?

320
00:17:02,321 --> 00:17:03,489
-No.
-Three, two.

321
00:17:04,857 --> 00:17:05,891
Three and two?

322
00:17:05,958 --> 00:17:07,659
-Three and two.
-Okay.

323
00:17:09,094 --> 00:17:10,896
Finish in that position.

324
00:17:11,196 --> 00:17:12,031
Okay.

325
00:17:14,566 --> 00:17:20,005
<i>The plethora of things they do to ensure
the audience enjoys every single second,</i>

326
00:17:20,272 --> 00:17:23,175
<i>is what creates entertainment.</i>

327
00:17:25,110 --> 00:17:29,615
You guys shouldn't
look down too much during this song.

328
00:17:30,015 --> 00:17:32,351
-Because the light comes from above.
-Okay.

329
00:17:35,187 --> 00:17:37,122
<i>From senior to junior,</i>

330
00:17:37,956 --> 00:17:40,626
<i>these thoughts are passed down.</i>

331
00:17:47,566 --> 00:17:49,101
YOKOHAMA ARENA

332
00:17:49,168 --> 00:17:50,836
<i>July 19th.</i>

333
00:17:51,136 --> 00:17:56,275
<i>King & Prince's second-year tour
is finally about to begin.</i>

334
00:17:58,577 --> 00:18:03,415
TEN MINUTES UNTIL SHOWTIME

335
00:18:04,650 --> 00:18:07,619
<i>Until last year,
they were still a bit nervous,</i>

336
00:18:07,886 --> 00:18:09,488
<i>but look how they are this year.</i>

337
00:18:10,889 --> 00:18:12,524
Let's go.

338
00:18:12,591 --> 00:18:13,592
See you.

339
00:18:13,659 --> 00:18:15,594
Here I go. Bye.

340
00:18:16,929 --> 00:18:18,864
<i>They've matured this much</i>

341
00:18:19,064 --> 00:18:22,801
<i>thanks to each other and
what they've experienced this past year.</i>

342
00:18:23,836 --> 00:18:24,837
Bye.

343
00:18:27,606 --> 00:18:28,674
<i>That is why...</i>

344
00:18:33,011 --> 00:18:37,883
<i>...they began by expressing their feelings
for their other member.</i>

345
00:19:22,961 --> 00:19:24,830
<i>The stage is rotating.</i>

346
00:19:31,170 --> 00:19:33,338
<i>It's time for the mature King & Prince.</i>

347
00:20:23,388 --> 00:20:24,323
<i>And then...</i>

348
00:20:24,823 --> 00:20:26,725
<i>a song in memoriam.</i>

349
00:20:26,992 --> 00:20:32,831
{\an8}SONG POPULARIZED
BY THE FIRST JOHNNY'S GROUP

350
00:20:51,283 --> 00:20:53,452
It wasn't in the set list originally,

351
00:20:53,518 --> 00:20:59,324
but I really wanted it to reach the person
who is the most dear to us right now.

352
00:20:59,558 --> 00:21:00,759
So, I added it in.

353
00:21:05,364 --> 00:21:07,733
<i>He sang with the determination</i>

354
00:21:07,799 --> 00:21:11,203
<i>that they will stand on
their own two feet from now on.</i>

355
00:21:12,404 --> 00:21:14,206
We are...

356
00:21:14,640 --> 00:21:16,275
King &...

357
00:21:16,341 --> 00:21:18,577
Prince!

358
00:21:18,644 --> 00:21:20,045
Thank you!

359
00:21:20,112 --> 00:21:23,415
<i>They will once again embark on
a new journey.</i>

360
00:21:23,482 --> 00:21:25,951
Thank you so much!

361
00:21:27,386 --> 00:21:29,054
<i>On the next</i> Ride On Time<i>,</i>

362
00:21:29,855 --> 00:21:32,324
<i>They get a big opportunity
from a dear friend.</i>

363
00:21:34,059 --> 00:21:35,460
{\an8}<i>They battle the pressure...</i>

364
00:21:37,562 --> 00:21:38,730
{\an8}Nothing's easy.

365
00:21:39,097 --> 00:21:39,931
{\an8}It's hard.

366
00:21:41,199 --> 00:21:42,601
{\an8}<i>And on the big day,</i>

367
00:21:42,668 --> 00:21:44,836
{\an8}<i>something happens to Kishi's body.</i>

368
00:21:45,771 --> 00:21:48,140
{\an8}<i>Will they be able to overcome it all?</i>

369
00:21:49,541 --> 00:21:51,109
{\an8}<i>Meanwhile, in the brutal heat,</i>

370
00:21:51,443 --> 00:21:53,845
{\an8}<i>other members devote themselves to acting.</i>

371
00:21:54,446 --> 00:21:56,415
{\an8}I'll survive with fighting spirit.

372
00:21:57,582 --> 00:22:00,986
{\an8}<i>The promise they made
to someone precious empowers them.</i>

373
00:22:01,320 --> 00:22:05,490
I want to hurry up and make it overseas,
